author: WCAX News
title: Lt. Gen. Michael Dubie retiring today
text:
COLCHESTER, Vt. - The former leader of the Vermont National Guard will be retiring today.
This afternoon, there will be a private ceremony for Lt. Gen. Michael Dubie at Camp Johnson.
Dubie spent the last three years as deputy commander of the U.S. Northern Command in Colorado Springs.
Sen. Patrick Leahy will be presenting him with the Defense Distinguished Service Medal.
